text: Deadwood (Lakota: Ow√°yasuta; "To approve or confirm things") is a city in South Dakota, United States, and the county seat of Lawrence County. It is named after the dead trees found in its gulch. The population was 1,156 at the 2020 census. The entire city is a National Historic Landmark District, for its well-preserved Gold Rush-era architecture. == References == Category:Cities in South Dakota Category:County seats in South Dakota
title: Deadwood, South Dakota
